<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAMESE AMERICANS</font><br>
<tt>Fri May  9  7:55:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Thanks for the recommendation Gerald. Interestingly, I've had rather extensive contact with Vietnamese Americans since Nam.  In the early days after the war I was in Philadelphia for a while and many of the survivors were settling in that area.  More recently I had a job driving a taxi and I picked up a young asian business person who had to go to the airport.  During the trip and ensuing conversation I learned that this individual have come to the States when very young as a result of the entire family escaping on boats in the Indian ocean.  They were picked up by the french and eventually arrived in America.  After the startled silence following the personal and family history this young person related to me I expressed my desire to appologize to him personally for the way America had conducted the defense of his nation.  He looked embarrased and said I shouldn't take it so seriously.  I replied that I had seen his people and my people die for the country that had once been South Vietnam and to me it would always be something I would take seriously. Take care Gerald.  
